From: chat-template-patches
Subject: [Q3.6-10] auto_disable_thinking_with_tools kwarg (default OFF)

Targets: templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja (state after Q3.6-1..Q3.6-6 applied)

Status: OPT-IN. NOT applied to the shipped patched/35B-A3B.jinja. A default-OFF
kwarg; even if applied it is a no-op until set. Offered as an alternative
*prevention* strategy to Q3.6-3's *recovery* (auto-close): some deployments
prefer to disable reasoning entirely while tools are in play rather than rely
on closing a leaked <think> before <tool_call>.

Behavior. When `auto_disable_thinking_with_tools=true` AND tools are present,
force thinking off (the generation prompt emits the closed
`<think>\n\n</think>\n\n` form). This is the Qwen3.6 analog of P7 (Qwen3.5:
auto-disable thinking when tools defined), exposed as froggeric's v20 kwarg of
the same name rather than an unconditional flip.

Precedence (verified). kwarg seed -> auto_disable (this patch) -> `<|think_off|>`/
`<|think_on|>` sentinels (Q3.6-5). The block is inserted BEFORE sentinel
detection, so an explicit `<|think_on|>` still overrides auto_disable. With the
kwarg unset the render is byte-identical to the shipped template.

Scope note. Whether to prefer prevention (this) or recovery (Q3.6-3) is
deployment-specific; both can coexist (auto_disable simply means the leak path
is rarely reached). Default OFF keeps Q3.6-3 the shipped behavior.

Prior art: froggeric Qwen-Fixed-Chat-Templates v20 (`auto_disable_thinking_with_tools`),
snapshotted at docs/sources/hf-snapshots/froggeric-Qwen-Fixed-Chat-Templates-v20.jinja.
Sibling: P7 (Qwen3.5).

Stacks on Q3.6-1..Q3.6-6. Diff is against the Q3.6-6-applied state.

--- a/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
+++ b/templates/qwen3.6/patched/35B-A3B.jinja
@@ -46,6 +46,10 @@
 {%- set ns_flags = namespace(enable_thinking=none) %}
 {%- if enable_thinking is defined %}
     {%- set ns_flags.enable_thinking = enable_thinking %}
+{%- endif %}
+{#- Q3.6-10 (opt-in): auto_disable_thinking_with_tools — when set and tools are present, force thinking OFF (P7-analog: prevents tool_call leakage inside <think>). Placed before sentinel detection so an explicit <|think_on|> still overrides. Default unset = no-op. -#}
+{%- if auto_disable_thinking_with_tools is defined and auto_disable_thinking_with_tools and tools and tools is iterable and tools is not mapping %}
+    {%- set ns_flags.enable_thinking = false %}
 {%- endif %}
 {%- set num_sys = 0 %}
 {%- set merged_system = '' %}
